1
00:00:01,460 --> 00:00:04,505
(WHOOSHING)

2
00:00:12,429 --> 00:00:14,223
(HORN BLARING)

3
00:00:22,189 --> 00:00:23,357
What?

4
00:00:25,609 --> 00:00:26,985
What?

5
00:00:27,069 --> 00:00:29,446
(BELL RINGING)

6
00:00:34,368 --> 00:00:35,911
What?

7
00:01:05,857 --> 00:01:08,277
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)

8
00:01:08,360 --> 00:01:11,530
(BAND PLAYING CHRISTMAS CAROL)

9
00:01:16,159 --> 00:01:18,161
You're very welcome.

10
00:01:39,975 --> 00:01:42,060
Christmas is funny...

11
00:01:49,401 --> 00:01:51,153
Right.

12
00:01:52,195 --> 00:01:54,197
ON PA: Attention all passengers.

13
00:01:54,281 --> 00:01:57,534
The Titanic ls now in orbit above Sol 3,

14
00:01:57,618 --> 00:02:01,747
also known as Earth. Population, human.

15
00:02:02,372 --> 00:02:06,043
Ladies and gentlemen,
welcome to Christmas.

16
00:02:10,255 --> 00:02:12,466
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

17
00:02:57,594 --> 00:02:59,513
Orbit nice and steady?

18
00:03:01,515 --> 00:03:05,602
Good work, Mr Cavrille,
and maintain position.

19
00:03:06,311 --> 00:03:10,148
Now then, gentlemen, according to
the traditions of the planet below,

20
00:03:10,232 --> 00:03:13,443
Christmas is a time of celebration.

21
00:03:13,527 --> 00:03:16,154
I think you might be entitled
to a tot of rum.

22
00:03:16,279 --> 00:03:17,781
Just the one.

23
00:03:18,699 --> 00:03:20,784
-Off you go.
-Sir.

24
00:03:20,909 --> 00:03:22,369
-Sir.
-Sir.

25
00:03:23,954 --> 00:03:26,289
-I'll keep watch.
-Sir.

26
00:03:35,924 --> 00:03:38,051
And you...what was it?

27
00:03:38,135 --> 00:03:40,262
Midshipman Frame, sir.

28
00:03:40,345 --> 00:03:44,015
I only just qualified, sir.
First trip out.

29
00:03:44,099 --> 00:03:46,727
Then you can stand down, Midshipman.

30
00:03:46,810 --> 00:03:48,603
(STUTTERING)

31
00:03:48,687 --> 00:03:51,356
But regulations say
the bridge has to be staffed

32
00:03:51,440 --> 00:03:54,526
by two crew members
at any one time, sir.

33
00:03:55,152 --> 00:03:57,154
Well said. Very good.

34
00:04:00,824 --> 00:04:05,620
Well, it should be nice and quiet.
It's only a Level 5 planet down below.

35
00:04:06,371 --> 00:04:09,249
They don't even know we're here.

36
00:04:10,500 --> 00:04:13,336
Silent night, I believe they call it.

37
00:04:14,838 --> 00:04:16,339
A silent night.

38
00:04:21,344 --> 00:04:24,681
Max Capricorn Cruiseliners.

39
00:04:24,765 --> 00:04:27,392
The fastest the furthest

40
00:04:28,143 --> 00:04:29,936
the best.

41
00:04:30,020 --> 00:04:32,439
And I should know because

42
00:04:32,522 --> 00:04:35,400
my name is Max.

43
00:04:37,068 --> 00:04:40,363
(WINTER WONDERLAND PLAYING)

44
00:04:44,576 --> 00:04:47,037
-Merry Christmas, sir.
-Merry Christmas.

45
00:05:09,726 --> 00:05:14,189
It's not a holiday for me,
not while I've still got my vone.

46
00:05:14,272 --> 00:05:16,900
Now, do as I say and sell.

47
00:05:18,902 --> 00:05:23,573
Evening, passenger 57, terrible memory.
Remind me, you would be?

48
00:05:23,657 --> 00:05:25,242
Information.

49
00:05:25,325 --> 00:05:29,120
Heavenly Host
supplying tourist information.

50
00:05:29,913 --> 00:05:33,834
Good. So, um, tell me,
'cause I'm an idiot.

51
00:05:33,917 --> 00:05:35,961
Where are we from?

52
00:05:36,044 --> 00:05:37,587
Information.

53
00:05:37,671 --> 00:05:40,924
The Titanic ls en route
from the planet Sto

54
00:05:41,007 --> 00:05:43,844
in the Casivanian Belt.

55
00:05:43,927 --> 00:05:49,266
The purpose of the cruise
is to experience primitive cultures.

56
00:05:49,891 --> 00:05:53,520
Titanic. Um, who thought of the name?

57
00:05:53,603 --> 00:05:55,188
Information.

58
00:05:55,272 --> 00:05:59,317
It was chosen as the most famous vessel
of the planet Earth.

59
00:05:59,401 --> 00:06:01,152
Did they tell you why it was famous?

60
00:06:01,236 --> 00:06:02,737
Information.

61
00:06:02,821 --> 00:06:06,575
All designations are chosen
by Mr Max Capricorn,

62
00:06:06,658 --> 00:06:09,035
President of Max... Max...

63
00:06:09,119 --> 00:06:12,289
(MALFUNCTIONING) Max... Max... Max...

64
00:06:12,372 --> 00:06:15,750
-Ooh. A bit of a glitch.
-Sorry, chaps, we can handle this.

65
00:06:15,834 --> 00:06:19,880
Max... Max... Max...

66
00:06:19,963 --> 00:06:22,799
Software problem, that's all.
Leave it with us, sir.

67
00:06:22,883 --> 00:06:25,218
Merry Christmas.

68
00:06:25,302 --> 00:06:28,680
That's another one down.
What's going on with these things?

69
00:06:30,849 --> 00:06:33,059
That's eight of them now on the blink.

70
00:06:33,143 --> 00:06:35,312
One woman, she asked the Host
to fix her necklace,

71
00:06:35,395 --> 00:06:37,314
it almost broke her neck.

72
00:06:37,480 --> 00:06:38,815
In first class.

73
00:06:38,940 --> 00:06:41,484
I've been over the robotics, nothing.

74
00:06:41,568 --> 00:06:44,654
It's like something's got into them.
Some kind of bug.

75
00:06:44,738 --> 00:06:49,534
Whoa! Wait, wait, wait!
Over there, in bay 15.

76
00:06:49,659 --> 00:06:53,455
Tell you what, if you can't fix them,
throw them overboard.

77
00:07:03,632 --> 00:07:05,008
(GLASS SHATTERING)

78
00:07:05,175 --> 00:07:07,344
For toff's sake!
Look where you're going.

79
00:07:07,469 --> 00:07:12,098
-This jacket's a genuine Earth antique.
-I'm sorry, sir.

80
00:07:12,182 --> 00:07:15,518
You'll be sorry when
it comes off your wages, sweetheart.

81
00:07:15,602 --> 00:07:20,607
Staffed by idiots. No wonder
Max Capricorn is going down the drain.

82
00:07:22,359 --> 00:07:24,361
Careful, there we go.

83
00:07:24,486 --> 00:07:27,364
-Thank you, sir, I can manage.
-I never said you couldn't.

84
00:07:27,447 --> 00:07:30,825
-I'm the Doctor, by the way.
-Astrid, sir. Astrid Peth.

85
00:07:30,909 --> 00:07:33,286
Nice to meet you, Astrid,
Merry Christmas.

86
00:07:33,370 --> 00:07:37,332
-Merry Christmas, sir.
-Just Doctor, not "sir".

87
00:07:37,415 --> 00:07:39,417
You enjoying the cruise?

88
00:07:39,501 --> 00:07:42,504
Um, yeah. I suppose. I don't know.

89
00:07:43,296 --> 00:07:46,257
It doesn't quite work,
a cruise on your own.

90
00:07:46,341 --> 00:07:49,886
-You're not with anyone?
-No, no, just me. Just...

91
00:07:49,970 --> 00:07:52,639
Used to be, but...

92
00:07:52,722 --> 00:07:56,601
No. What about you?
Long way from home, planet Sto.

93
00:07:56,685 --> 00:07:58,728
Doesn't feel that different.

94
00:07:58,853 --> 00:08:01,064
Spent three years working
at the Spaceport Diner.

95
00:08:01,189 --> 00:08:04,818
Travelled all the way here
and I'm still waiting on tables.

96
00:08:07,278 --> 00:08:08,780
No shore leave?

97
00:08:08,863 --> 00:08:11,908
We're not allowed.
They can't afford the insurance.

98
00:08:11,992 --> 00:08:14,536
I just wanted to try it, just once.

99
00:08:15,578 --> 00:08:18,123
I used to watch the ships
heading out to the stars.

100
00:08:18,206 --> 00:08:20,417
I always dreamt of...

101
00:08:21,543 --> 00:08:25,588
-Sounds daft.
-You dreamt of another sky.

102
00:08:25,672 --> 00:08:29,217
New sun, new air, new life.

103
00:08:30,844 --> 00:08:33,680
A whole universe teeming with life.

104
00:08:34,347 --> 00:08:38,476
(SIGHS) Why stand still
when there's all that life out there?

105
00:08:42,564 --> 00:08:46,776
-So, you travel a lot?
-All the time. Just for fun.

106
00:08:46,943 --> 00:08:49,863
Well, that's the plan.
Never quite works.

107
00:08:51,573 --> 00:08:54,617
-Must be rich, though.
-Haven't got a penny.

108
00:08:56,369 --> 00:08:57,912
(WHISPERS) Stowaway.

109
00:08:58,955 --> 00:09:00,540
-Kidding?
-Seriously.

110
00:09:00,623 --> 00:09:02,292
-No!
-Oh, yeah.

111
00:09:02,375 --> 00:09:04,377
-How'd you get on board?
-Accident.

112
00:09:04,461 --> 00:09:07,839
I've got this, sort of,
ship thing, I was just rebuilding...

113
00:09:07,922 --> 00:09:11,801
Left the defences down.
Bumped into the Titanic, here I am.

114
00:09:12,302 --> 00:09:15,013
A bit of a party, I thought, why not?

115
00:09:15,972 --> 00:09:19,851
-I should report you.
-Go on, then.

116
00:09:22,312 --> 00:09:23,855
I'll get you a drink.

117
00:09:23,938 --> 00:09:26,024
(WHISPERS) On the house.

118
00:09:35,575 --> 00:09:38,578
-Just ignore them.
-Something's tickled them.

119
00:09:38,661 --> 00:09:41,122
They told us it was fancy dress.

120
00:09:41,915 --> 00:09:43,333
Very funny, I'm sure.

121
00:09:43,416 --> 00:09:45,919
They're just picking on us
because we haven't paid.

122
00:09:46,002 --> 00:09:48,129
We won our tickets in a competition.

123
00:09:48,213 --> 00:09:51,174
I had to name the five husbands
of Juthy Crystal

124
00:09:51,257 --> 00:09:53,635
in By the Light of the Asteroid.

125
00:09:53,718 --> 00:09:55,887
Do you ever watch
By the Light of the Asteroid?

126
00:09:55,970 --> 00:09:59,265
-Is that the one with the twins?
-That's it. Oh, it's marvellous.

127
00:09:59,349 --> 00:10:03,436
But we're not good enough for that lot.
They think we should be in steerage.

128
00:10:03,520 --> 00:10:06,022
Can't have that, can we?

129
00:10:11,820 --> 00:10:13,488
-Did you do that?
-Maybe.

130
00:10:13,571 --> 00:10:16,032
(BOTH CHUCKLING)

131
00:10:16,116 --> 00:10:18,284
-We like you.
-We do.

132
00:10:18,868 --> 00:10:22,330
I'm Morvin Van Hoff.
This is my good woman, Foon.

133
00:10:22,413 --> 00:10:24,541
Foon. Hello, I'm the Doctor.

134
00:10:24,707 --> 00:10:27,794
Oh, well, I'll need a doctor
by the time I finish with that buffet.

135
00:10:27,877 --> 00:10:31,214
Have a buffalo wing.
They must be enormous, these buffalo.

136
00:10:31,297 --> 00:10:32,966
So many wings.

137
00:10:34,217 --> 00:10:39,305
ON PA: Attention, please. Shore leave
tickets Red 6-7 now activated.

138
00:10:39,389 --> 00:10:41,641
-Red 6-7.
-Red 6-77?

139
00:10:41,724 --> 00:10:43,476
-That's us.
-Thank you.

140
00:10:43,560 --> 00:10:45,979
-Are you Red 6-77?
-Might as well be.

141
00:10:46,062 --> 00:10:47,730
Come on, then.

142
00:10:48,690 --> 00:10:50,733
We're going to Earth.

143
00:10:56,698 --> 00:10:58,700
(RAPID BEEPING)

144
00:11:00,076 --> 00:11:03,788
Seems to be power diverted
to Deck 31, sir.

145
00:11:03,913 --> 00:11:05,582
Flared up, then it stopped.

146
00:11:05,665 --> 00:11:10,837
Nothing to worry about. She's
an old ship, full of aches and pains.

147
00:11:10,920 --> 00:11:16,384
Picking up a meteoroid shower,
port side, bearing west 56, north 2.

148
00:11:16,467 --> 00:11:20,305
Very standard in this part of space,
miles away.

149
00:11:20,388 --> 00:11:22,807
We could probably see it, sir.

150
00:11:26,603 --> 00:11:32,066
Red 6-7. Red 6-7, this way.
Fast as you can.

151
00:11:32,442 --> 00:11:34,819
-I got you that drink.
-And I got you a treat, come on.

152
00:11:34,944 --> 00:11:37,238
Red 6-7, departing shortly.

153
00:11:37,322 --> 00:11:40,033
-Red 6-7, plus one.
-Uh...

154
00:11:40,116 --> 00:11:44,287
Quickly, sir, please, and take
two teleport bracelets if you would.

155
00:11:44,370 --> 00:11:46,372
-I'll get the sack.
-Brand new sky.

156
00:11:46,456 --> 00:11:50,501
To repeat. I am Mr Copper,
the ship's historian,

157
00:11:51,419 --> 00:11:56,466
and I shall be taking you to
old London Town in the country of UK,

158
00:11:57,675 --> 00:12:01,596
ruled over by Good King Wenceslas.

159
00:12:01,679 --> 00:12:05,308
Now, human beings
worship the great god Santa,

160
00:12:05,391 --> 00:12:09,979
a creature with fearsome claws,
and his wife Mary.

161
00:12:10,813 --> 00:12:14,734
And every Christmas Eve,
the people of UK go to war

162
00:12:14,817 --> 00:12:16,903
with the country of Turkey.

163
00:12:16,986 --> 00:12:21,658
They then eat the Turkey people
for Christmas dinner,

164
00:12:21,741 --> 00:12:23,493
like savages.

165
00:12:24,452 --> 00:12:29,165
Excuse me, sorry, sorry. But, um,
where did you get all this from?

166
00:12:29,290 --> 00:12:33,294
Well, I have a first class degree
in Earthonomics. Now, standby...

167
00:12:33,378 --> 00:12:35,964
And me! And me! Red 6-7.

168
00:12:36,047 --> 00:12:38,633
COPPER: Take a bracelet, please, sir.

169
00:12:38,716 --> 00:12:41,344
But, hold on, hold on.
What was your name?

170
00:12:41,427 --> 00:12:43,346
Bannakaffalatta.

171
00:12:43,429 --> 00:12:46,766
Okay, Bannakaffalatta.
But it's Christmas Eve down there.

172
00:12:46,849 --> 00:12:49,894
Late-night shopping, tons of people.
He's like a talking conker.

173
00:12:49,978 --> 00:12:52,855
No offence, but you'll cause a riot,
'cause the streets are gonna be packed

174
00:12:52,939 --> 00:12:55,608
with shoppers and parties and...

175
00:12:56,276 --> 00:12:57,402
Oh.

176
00:12:57,485 --> 00:13:02,323
Now as spending money,
I have a credit card in Earth currency.

177
00:13:02,407 --> 00:13:06,077
If you want to buy trinkets or stockings

178
00:13:06,202 --> 00:13:10,206
or the local delicacy,
which is known as beef.

179
00:13:10,290 --> 00:13:13,584
But don't stray too far,
it could be dangerous.

180
00:13:13,668 --> 00:13:16,045
Any day now, they start boxing.

181
00:13:16,254 --> 00:13:18,798
It should be full.

182
00:13:18,881 --> 00:13:21,092
It should be busy. Something's wrong.

183
00:13:21,175 --> 00:13:23,011
But it's beautiful.

184
00:13:23,886 --> 00:13:27,473
Really? Do you think so?
It's just a street.

185
00:13:27,557 --> 00:13:30,852
The pyramids are beautiful,
and New Zealand.

186
00:13:30,935 --> 00:13:34,480
But it's a different planet.
I'm standing on a different planet!

187
00:13:34,564 --> 00:13:36,441
(STAMMERING) There's concrete

188
00:13:36,524 --> 00:13:40,153
and shops, alien shops,
real alien shops!

189
00:13:40,236 --> 00:13:42,780
Look, no stars in the sky.

190
00:13:43,239 --> 00:13:46,075
And it smells. It stinks!

191
00:13:46,159 --> 00:13:49,037
Oh, this is amazing! Thank you.

192
00:13:49,120 --> 00:13:51,831
Yeah? Come on, then. Let's have a look.

193
00:13:54,042 --> 00:13:57,503
Hello, there. Sorry, obvious question.

194
00:13:57,587 --> 00:14:00,673
-But where's everybody gone?
-Whoa. Scared.

195
00:14:00,757 --> 00:14:03,259
Right, yes. Scared of what?

196
00:14:03,343 --> 00:14:05,470
Where have you been living?

197
00:14:05,595 --> 00:14:09,140
London, at Christmas. Not safe, is it?

198
00:14:09,599 --> 00:14:12,769
-Why?
-Well, it's them, up above.

199
00:14:13,603 --> 00:14:17,732
Look, Christmas before last,
we had that big bloody spaceship,

200
00:14:17,815 --> 00:14:20,693
everyone standing on the roof,
and then last year,

201
00:14:20,777 --> 00:14:24,697
that Christmas star
electrocuting all over the place.

202
00:14:24,781 --> 00:14:28,618
-Draining the Thames.
-This place is amazing.

203
00:14:28,701 --> 00:14:32,413
And this year, God knows what.
So, everybody's scarpered.

204
00:14:32,497 --> 00:14:37,627
Gone to the country.
All except me, and Her Majesty.

205
00:14:37,710 --> 00:14:40,421
Her Majesty the Queen has confirmed
that she'll be staying

206
00:14:40,505 --> 00:14:43,091
in Buckingham Palace
throughout the festive season

207
00:14:43,174 --> 00:14:45,802
to show the people of London
and the world

208
00:14:45,885 --> 00:14:47,428
that there's nothing to fear.

209
00:14:47,512 --> 00:14:51,641
God bless her. We stand vigil.

210
00:14:51,724 --> 00:14:55,978
Well, between you and me,
I think Her Majesty's got it right.

211
00:14:56,062 --> 00:14:59,107
As far as I know, this year,
nothing to worry about.

212
00:15:06,406 --> 00:15:07,990
Then again.

213
00:15:08,074 --> 00:15:13,121
-I was in mid-sentence.
-Yes, I'm sorry about that.

214
00:15:13,204 --> 00:15:15,957
Bit of a problem.
If I can have your brace...

215
00:15:16,040 --> 00:15:18,835
Apologies, ladies and gentlemen,
Bannakaffalatta.

216
00:15:18,918 --> 00:15:22,422
We seem to have suffered
a power fluctuation.

217
00:15:22,505 --> 00:15:24,757
If you'd like to
return to the festivities,

218
00:15:24,841 --> 00:15:27,927
and on behalf of
Max Capricorn Cruiseliners,

219
00:15:28,010 --> 00:15:30,763
free drinks will be provided.

220
00:15:31,222 --> 00:15:33,349
FOON: Thank you.

221
00:15:33,474 --> 00:15:35,643
That was the best. The best.

222
00:15:38,980 --> 00:15:41,357
What sort of power fluctuation?

223
00:15:49,031 --> 00:15:52,827
That's a bit odd, sir.
The meteoroids are changing course.

224
00:15:53,911 --> 00:15:56,914
Still, we can put the shields
up to maximum, just in case.

225
00:15:57,039 --> 00:15:59,083
As you were, Midshipman.

226
00:16:00,918 --> 00:16:02,336
Sir?

227
00:16:03,087 --> 00:16:04,505
(BEEPING)

228
00:16:04,589 --> 00:16:07,842
You're magnetising the hull, sir.
It's drawing the meteors in.

229
00:16:07,925 --> 00:16:09,594
ELECTRONIC VOICE:
Port turning Earth-side.

230
00:16:09,677 --> 00:16:12,096
-FRAME: I take it that's deliberate.
-Port turning Earth-side.

231
00:16:12,180 --> 00:16:14,849
A bit of a lights how for the guests?

232
00:16:17,852 --> 00:16:19,645
Something like that.

233
00:16:22,273 --> 00:16:25,067
(SINGING THE STOWAWAY)

234
00:16:48,591 --> 00:16:53,763
And I should know
because my name is Max.

235
00:16:56,349 --> 00:17:00,895
The fastest the furthest the best.

236
00:17:00,978 --> 00:17:04,357
My name is Max.

237
00:17:23,417 --> 00:17:26,003
(INTERCOM WHISTLING)

238
00:17:26,128 --> 00:17:27,880
DOCTOR: Is that the bridge?
I need to talk to the Captain.

239
00:17:27,964 --> 00:17:30,508
You got a meteoroid storm coming in.
West 0 by north 2.

240
00:17:30,591 --> 00:17:32,552
-Who is this?
-Never mind that. Your shields are down.

241
00:17:32,635 --> 00:17:33,844
Check your scanners, Captain.

242
00:17:33,970 --> 00:17:36,305
You got meteoroids coming in
and no shielding.

243
00:17:36,430 --> 00:17:39,016
You have no authorisation.
You will clear the comms at once.

244
00:17:39,141 --> 00:17:40,476
Yeah? Just look starboard!

245
00:17:40,601 --> 00:17:42,937
If you would come with me, sir.

246
00:17:44,855 --> 00:17:47,900
But he's right, sir.
The shields have been taken off-line.

247
00:17:47,984 --> 00:17:50,528
-Step away from there.
-We have to re-energise, sir.

248
00:17:50,653 --> 00:17:53,114
I said, step away, Midshipman.

249
00:17:56,158 --> 00:17:59,495
You've got a rock storm heading for
the ship and the shields are down!

250
00:18:03,874 --> 00:18:07,211
-They promised me old men.
-I'm sorry, sir?

251
00:18:07,878 --> 00:18:12,717
On the crew, sea dogs,
men who'd had their time. Not boys.

252
00:18:13,843 --> 00:18:16,053
(THE STOWAWAY PLAYING)

253
00:18:19,765 --> 00:18:22,977
Listen to me. This is an emergency.
Get to the life...

254
00:18:23,811 --> 00:18:26,022
I'm sorry, sir. It's my duty.

255
00:18:29,108 --> 00:18:31,027
Look out the windows!

256
00:18:41,329 --> 00:18:42,913
Run for it.

257
00:18:46,542 --> 00:18:49,128
If you don't believe me,
then check the shields yourself.

258
00:18:49,211 --> 00:18:50,796
Sir, I can vouch for him.

259
00:18:50,880 --> 00:18:52,673
Steward, he's just had
a bit too much to drink.

260
00:18:52,757 --> 00:18:55,926
Sir, something seems to have gone wrong.
All the teleports have gone down.

261
00:18:56,010 --> 00:18:57,428
Not now.

262
00:19:01,474 --> 00:19:06,646
ELECTRONIC VOICE: Oxygen membrane
holding. Oxygen membrane holding.

263
00:19:06,729 --> 00:19:10,775
You, there. Has anyone checked
the external shielding?

264
00:19:10,858 --> 00:19:12,318
Information.

265
00:19:12,401 --> 00:19:14,612
You are all going to die.

266
00:19:31,420 --> 00:19:34,382
-Where's the Chief Steward?
-He went that way, sir.

267
00:19:35,549 --> 00:19:38,177
The shields are down!
We are going to get hit!

268
00:19:38,260 --> 00:19:39,679
It seems to be working...

269
00:19:39,762 --> 00:19:41,472
You're going to kill us.

270
00:19:42,056 --> 00:19:43,599
I'm dying already.

271
00:19:45,935 --> 00:19:50,272
Six months.
They offered me so much money.

272
00:19:53,609 --> 00:19:55,277
For my family.

273
00:19:55,403 --> 00:19:59,323
Oi, Steward!
I'm telling you, the shields are down.

274
00:19:59,407 --> 00:20:01,117
Listen to him. Listen to him!

275
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:02,868
Max Capricorn.

276
00:20:04,120 --> 00:20:06,455
Darling, come and have a look at this.

277
00:20:07,289 --> 00:20:08,791
The fastest...

278
00:20:09,583 --> 00:20:12,503
ELECTRONIC VOICE: Red alert. Red alert.

279
00:20:15,673 --> 00:20:16,966
...the furthest...

280
00:20:19,927 --> 00:20:21,387
the best.

281
00:20:23,305 --> 00:20:24,473
The best.

282
00:21:08,768 --> 00:21:10,644
MAN: Oh, God!

283
00:21:11,353 --> 00:21:12,855
It won't budge.

284
00:21:15,024 --> 00:21:16,692
Help me!

285
00:21:17,651 --> 00:21:18,861
Help...

286
00:21:32,708 --> 00:21:35,127
MORVIN: It's all right.
It's all right, sweetheart.

287
00:21:35,211 --> 00:21:37,379
(FOON WHIMPERING)

288
00:21:37,797 --> 00:21:39,423
Shh!

289
00:21:45,554 --> 00:21:46,931
It's stopping.

290
00:21:47,223 --> 00:21:49,475
(CREAKING)

291
00:21:54,355 --> 00:21:57,233
-You all right?
-I think so.

292
00:21:58,067 --> 00:21:59,902
Bad name for a ship.

293
00:22:00,528 --> 00:22:03,739
Either that,
or this suit is really unlucky.

294
00:22:03,823 --> 00:22:10,538
CAPRICORN ON TV: My name is Max.
My name is Max...

295
00:22:10,704 --> 00:22:13,666
Everyone, ladies and gentlemen,
Bannakaffalatta.

296
00:22:13,749 --> 00:22:17,086
I must apologise on behalf of
Max Capricorn Cruiseliners.

297
00:22:17,169 --> 00:22:19,505
-We seem to have had a small collision.
-Small?

298
00:22:19,588 --> 00:22:20,798
Do you know how much I paid...

299
00:22:20,923 --> 00:22:23,509
-...how much I paid for my ticket?
-If I could have silence, ladies.

300
00:22:23,592 --> 00:22:26,303
(ALL CLAMOURING)

301
00:22:26,428 --> 00:22:27,596
Quiet!

302
00:22:28,347 --> 00:22:29,473
Thank you.

303
00:22:29,557 --> 00:22:32,309
I'm sure Max Capricorn Cruiseliners

304
00:22:32,434 --> 00:22:35,229
will be able to reimburse you
for any inconvenience.

305
00:22:35,312 --> 00:22:39,066
But, first, I would point out
that we're very much alive.

306
00:22:39,149 --> 00:22:42,695
It is, after all,
a fine and sturdy ship.

307
00:22:42,778 --> 00:22:45,114
If you could all stay here

308
00:22:45,239 --> 00:22:51,328
while I ascertain the exact nature
of the situation.

309
00:22:52,705 --> 00:22:54,290
Don't open it!

310
00:23:13,434 --> 00:23:15,728
Oxygen shield stabilised.

311
00:23:15,811 --> 00:23:18,188
-Everyone all right? Astrid?
-Yeah.

312
00:23:18,272 --> 00:23:20,232
-Foon? Morvin?
-Yeah.

313
00:23:20,316 --> 00:23:23,193
-Mr Copper? Bannakaffalatta?
-Yes.

314
00:23:24,320 --> 00:23:26,280
-You, what was your name?
-Rickston Slade.

315
00:23:26,363 --> 00:23:29,491
-You all right?
-Yeah. No thanks to that idiot.

316
00:23:29,575 --> 00:23:33,162
-The steward just died.
-Then he's a dead idiot.

317
00:23:33,287 --> 00:23:37,750
All right, calm down.
Just stay still, all of you, hold on.

318
00:23:42,338 --> 00:23:44,423
What happened?
How come the shields were down?

319
00:23:44,506 --> 00:23:47,092
I don't think it was an accident.

320
00:23:49,261 --> 00:23:53,432
-How many dead?
-We're alive, just focus on that.

321
00:23:54,141 --> 00:23:58,270
I will get you out of here, Astrid.
I promise. Look at me.

322
00:23:59,772 --> 00:24:02,524
I promise. Good.

323
00:24:02,650 --> 00:24:05,861
Now, if we can get to reception,
I've got a spaceship tucked away.

324
00:24:05,986 --> 00:24:07,655
We can all get on board...

325
00:24:07,738 --> 00:24:10,699
-Oh.
-What is it? What's wrong?

326
00:24:11,575 --> 00:24:13,953
-That's my ship over there.
-Where?

327
00:24:14,036 --> 00:24:16,914
There, that box. That little blue box.

328
00:24:17,414 --> 00:24:20,334
-That's a spaceship?
-0i, don't knock it.

329
00:24:20,459 --> 00:24:22,962
-It's a bit small.
-A bit distant.

330
00:24:23,379 --> 00:24:25,714
Trouble is, once it's set adrift,

331
00:24:25,798 --> 00:24:28,384
it's programmed to lock onto
the nearest centre of gravity

332
00:24:28,467 --> 00:24:31,804
and that would be the Earth.

333
00:24:45,567 --> 00:24:48,821
Don't just stand there.
Get this thing off me.

334
00:24:49,822 --> 00:24:54,034
Host, that's an order, help me.
That is your job, isn't it?

335
00:24:55,369 --> 00:24:57,037
Information.

336
00:24:57,162 --> 00:24:59,748
We now have only one function.

337
00:25:00,749 --> 00:25:02,001
And what's that?

338
00:25:02,084 --> 00:25:03,752
Information.

339
00:25:03,877 --> 00:25:05,212
To kill.

340
00:25:06,505 --> 00:25:09,633
What are you doing? Host?

341
00:25:09,758 --> 00:25:12,678
I'm ordering you. Stop it!

342
00:25:12,761 --> 00:25:14,513
Stop it right now!

343
00:25:15,931 --> 00:25:18,350
Deck 22 to the bridge.

344
00:25:19,309 --> 00:25:21,603
Deck 22 to the bridge.
Is there anyone there?

345
00:25:21,729 --> 00:25:23,272
(GROANING)

346
00:25:23,397 --> 00:25:24,857
This is the bridge.

347
00:25:24,940 --> 00:25:29,361
Oh! Hello, sailor, good to hear you.
What's the situation up there?

348
00:25:29,737 --> 00:25:31,405
(GROANING)

349
00:25:31,488 --> 00:25:34,783
We've got air,
the oxygen field is holding.

350
00:25:34,867 --> 00:25:37,745
But the Captain, he's dead.

351
00:25:39,538 --> 00:25:43,417
He did it! Wasn't my fault
he took down the shields.

352
00:25:43,542 --> 00:25:45,753
There was nothing I could do.
I tried. I did try.

353
00:25:45,836 --> 00:25:48,547
All right, just stay calm.
Tell me your name. What's your name?

354
00:25:48,630 --> 00:25:50,632
Midshipman Frame.

355
00:25:50,716 --> 00:25:53,677
Nice to meet you, sir.
What's the state of the engines?

356
00:25:53,802 --> 00:25:55,095
They're...

357
00:25:58,015 --> 00:25:59,308
Hold on.

358
00:26:00,392 --> 00:26:02,978
(SCREAMING IN PAIN)

359
00:26:03,645 --> 00:26:06,315
-Have you been injured?
-I'm all right.

360
00:26:07,566 --> 00:26:10,527
Oh, my God. They're cycling down.

361
00:26:12,529 --> 00:26:15,783
-That's a nuclear storm drive, yes?
-Yes.

362
00:26:15,866 --> 00:26:17,993
The moment they're gone, we lose orbit.

363
00:26:18,077 --> 00:26:20,120
-The planet.
-Oh, yes.

364
00:26:20,871 --> 00:26:23,165
If we hit the planet,
the nuclear storm will explode

365
00:26:23,248 --> 00:26:24,833
and wipe out life on Earth.

366
00:26:27,586 --> 00:26:29,797
(CREAKING)

367
00:26:32,257 --> 00:26:35,010
Midshipman, I need you to fire up
the engine containment field

368
00:26:35,135 --> 00:26:36,804
and feed it back into the core.

369
00:26:36,887 --> 00:26:38,847
This is never going to work.

370
00:26:38,972 --> 00:26:41,558
Trust me. It'll keep the engines going
till I can get to the bridge.

371
00:26:41,683 --> 00:26:43,393
-We're going to die.
-Are you saying...

372
00:26:43,519 --> 00:26:45,354
FOON: We are. We're going to die!

373
00:26:45,479 --> 00:26:48,857
Okay! First things first.

374
00:26:48,982 --> 00:26:51,777
One, we're going to
climb through this ship.

375
00:26:51,860 --> 00:26:53,529
B... No.

376
00:26:53,654 --> 00:26:55,531
Two, we're going to reach the bridge.

377
00:26:55,614 --> 00:26:58,158
Three, or C,
we're going Yo save the Titanic.

378
00:26:58,242 --> 00:27:01,161
And coming in a very low four, or D,

379
00:27:01,245 --> 00:27:05,040
or that little IV in brackets
they use in foot notes... Why?

380
00:27:05,124 --> 00:27:07,960
-Right then, follow me.
-Hang on a minute.

381
00:27:08,043 --> 00:27:12,089
Who put you in charge?
And who the hell are you anyway?

382
00:27:14,216 --> 00:27:17,719
I'm the Doctor. I'm a Time Lord.

383
00:27:17,803 --> 00:27:21,014
I'm from the planet Gallifrey in
the constellation of Kasterborous.

384
00:27:21,098 --> 00:27:24,017
I'm 903 years old, and I'm the man
who's going to save your lives

385
00:27:24,101 --> 00:27:27,229
and all six billion people
on the planet below.

386
00:27:31,650 --> 00:27:34,278
-You have a problem with that?
-No.

387
00:27:34,403 --> 00:27:37,072
In that case, allons-y!

388
00:27:58,594 --> 00:27:59,845
Careful.

389
00:28:01,555 --> 00:28:03,098
Follow me.

390
00:28:04,892 --> 00:28:09,188
Rather ironic, but this is very much
in the spirit of Christmas.

391
00:28:09,271 --> 00:28:11,607
It's a festival of violence.

392
00:28:11,690 --> 00:28:16,320
They say that human beings only survive

393
00:28:16,445 --> 00:28:18,864
depending on whether
they've been good or bad.

394
00:28:18,947 --> 00:28:20,324
It's barbaric.

395
00:28:20,449 --> 00:28:21,783
Actually, that's not true.

396
00:28:21,909 --> 00:28:25,871
Christmas is a time of peace
and thanksgiving and...

397
00:28:25,954 --> 00:28:29,541
What am I on about?
My Christmases are always like this.

398
00:28:31,752 --> 00:28:33,712
We've got a Host.

399
00:28:33,837 --> 00:28:35,547
Strength of ten.

400
00:28:35,631 --> 00:28:38,008
If we can mend it,
we can use it to fix the rubble.

401
00:28:38,091 --> 00:28:40,177
We can do robotics, both of us.

402
00:28:40,260 --> 00:28:43,680
We work on the milk market back on Sto.
It's all robot staff.

403
00:28:43,764 --> 00:28:46,975
See if you can get it working.
Let's have a look.

404
00:28:53,482 --> 00:28:56,109
-ASTRID: It's blocked.
-So what do we do?

405
00:28:56,193 --> 00:28:58,654
-We shift it.
-That's the attitude.

406
00:28:58,737 --> 00:29:01,698
Rickston, Mr Copper
and you, Bannakaffalatta...

407
00:29:02,616 --> 00:29:05,035
Look, can I just call you Banna?
It's going to save a lot of time.

408
00:29:05,118 --> 00:29:07,162
No! Bannakaffalatta.

409
00:29:07,287 --> 00:29:09,706
All right then, Bannakaffalatta,
there's a gap in the middle,

410
00:29:09,831 --> 00:29:11,792
see if you can get through.

411
00:29:11,875 --> 00:29:13,543
Easy, good.

412
00:29:18,507 --> 00:29:21,301
This whole thing could
come crashing down any minute.

413
00:29:21,385 --> 00:29:23,220
Oh, Rickston, I forgot,
did you get that message?

414
00:29:23,303 --> 00:29:25,806
-No. What message?
-Shut up!

415
00:29:26,431 --> 00:29:28,350
Bannakaffalatta made it.

416
00:29:29,017 --> 00:29:31,853
-I'm small enough, I can get through.
-Careful.

417
00:29:31,937 --> 00:29:33,355
I'm fine.

418
00:29:35,107 --> 00:29:39,444
The thing is, how are Mr and Mrs Fatso
going to get through that gap?

419
00:29:39,528 --> 00:29:42,364
We make the gap bigger. So, start.

420
00:29:43,031 --> 00:29:47,035
Hey, hey. Come on, sweetheart.
Don't listen to him.

421
00:29:48,745 --> 00:29:52,249
No. But it's all my fault, though.
The tickets.

422
00:29:52,332 --> 00:29:55,168
-We won them fair and square.
-I know.

423
00:29:55,252 --> 00:29:57,087
I never told you.

424
00:29:58,130 --> 00:30:01,591
I dialled the competition line
5,000 times.

425
00:30:01,675 --> 00:30:03,760
That's 5,000 credits.

426
00:30:03,844 --> 00:30:06,221
I might as well have
paid for the tickets.

427
00:30:07,389 --> 00:30:10,642
I've been hiding the phone bill
for months now.

428
00:30:10,726 --> 00:30:12,436
5,000 credits?

429
00:30:14,354 --> 00:30:18,025
-You spent 5,000 credits?
-Don't hate me.

430
00:30:22,029 --> 00:30:24,114
(CHUCKLES)

431
00:30:30,370 --> 00:30:32,414
What's so funny?

432
00:30:32,497 --> 00:30:34,082
5,0007

433
00:30:35,334 --> 00:30:37,461
We'll never pay that off.

434
00:30:37,544 --> 00:30:41,590
I know. We'll have to work 20 years,
you mad bloody woman.

435
00:30:41,715 --> 00:30:42,883
(LAUGHING)

436
00:30:42,966 --> 00:30:45,677
-You're not cross?
-Does it matter?

437
00:30:46,386 --> 00:30:48,263
Look at us.

438
00:30:48,347 --> 00:30:50,098
You drive me barmy.

439
00:30:50,932 --> 00:30:53,310
I don't half love you.

440
00:30:53,435 --> 00:30:56,438
Mrs Van Hoff, come here.

441
00:31:01,985 --> 00:31:03,945
(VAN HOFFS LAUGHING)

442
00:31:04,029 --> 00:31:06,573
What happened? Did they find a doughnut?

443
00:31:06,656 --> 00:31:10,327
I can clear it from this side.
Just tell me if it starts moving.

444
00:31:13,705 --> 00:31:16,458
-Bannakaffalatta, what's wrong?
-Shh.

445
00:31:16,541 --> 00:31:18,627
-What is it?
-Can't say.

446
00:31:19,878 --> 00:31:21,588
Are you hurt?

447
00:31:21,671 --> 00:31:23,298
-Ashamed.
-Of what?

448
00:31:23,423 --> 00:31:25,592
Poor Bannakaffalatta.

449
00:31:27,844 --> 00:31:29,930
You're a cyborg.

450
00:31:31,056 --> 00:31:33,892
Had accident long ago.

451
00:31:33,975 --> 00:31:35,310
Secret.

452
00:31:35,394 --> 00:31:37,979
No, but everything's changed now.

453
00:31:38,105 --> 00:31:40,690
Cyborgs are getting equal rights.

454
00:31:40,774 --> 00:31:44,069
They passed a law back on Sto.
You can even get married.

455
00:31:44,152 --> 00:31:45,654
Marry you?

456
00:31:46,988 --> 00:31:49,366
Well, you can buy me a drink first.

457
00:31:50,033 --> 00:31:52,452
Come on, let's recharge you.

458
00:31:55,831 --> 00:31:58,417
Just stay there for a bit.

459
00:31:58,500 --> 00:32:01,086
-Tell no one.
-I promise.

460
00:32:01,920 --> 00:32:03,588
What's going on up there?

461
00:32:04,840 --> 00:32:08,260
Well, I think Bannakaffalatta and I
just got engaged.

462
00:32:11,012 --> 00:32:13,265
(INTERCOM WHISTLING)

463
00:32:17,018 --> 00:32:18,186
This is the bridge.

464
00:32:18,270 --> 00:32:19,521
This is kitchen number 5.

465
00:32:20,814 --> 00:32:23,608
-How many of you are there?
-Six of us, just about.

466
00:32:23,692 --> 00:32:25,318
Are we the only ones left alive, sir?

467
00:32:25,402 --> 00:32:29,030
No, there's more on Deck 19.
Hold on, if I reverse the scanner...

468
00:32:31,324 --> 00:32:34,411
Around 50, 60 people still alive
all over the ship.

469
00:32:34,536 --> 00:32:36,288
Hold on.

470
00:32:36,371 --> 00:32:39,624
I can see you.
Kitchen 05, there you are.

471
00:32:39,708 --> 00:32:42,586
Listen, everyone's heading
for the bridge.

472
00:32:42,669 --> 00:32:45,630
Don't go port side, there's no way.
Can you make your way starboard?

473
00:32:45,714 --> 00:32:48,717
We're stuck. The doors have sealed.
We can't get out.

474
00:32:50,552 --> 00:32:52,637
No, wait a minute. It's opening.

475
00:32:55,182 --> 00:32:57,058
There's someone on the other side.

476
00:33:01,062 --> 00:33:04,357
Host, we've got Host.
The Host are still working.

477
00:33:04,441 --> 00:33:08,111
Oh, that's brilliant.
Tell them to clear a path to the bridge.

478
00:33:10,071 --> 00:33:11,781
Did you get that?

479
00:33:12,616 --> 00:33:14,326
Kitchen 05, report.

480
00:33:15,535 --> 00:33:17,120
Hello, Kitchen 05?

481
00:33:17,329 --> 00:33:19,998
(SCREAMING)

482
00:33:21,374 --> 00:33:22,626
Report!

483
00:33:22,709 --> 00:33:24,586
-Almost done.
-Good, good, good.

484
00:33:24,711 --> 00:33:25,879
Mr Frame, how's things?

485
00:33:25,962 --> 00:33:28,298
Doctor, I've got life signs
all over the ship,

486
00:33:28,381 --> 00:33:30,884
but they're going out one by one.

487
00:33:30,967 --> 00:33:32,802
What is it? Are they losing air?

488
00:33:32,928 --> 00:33:35,931
No. Well, I'm not sure,
but it's the Host.

489
00:33:36,056 --> 00:33:38,600
It's something to do with the Host.

490
00:33:40,769 --> 00:33:42,729
It's working!

491
00:33:42,812 --> 00:33:45,607
-HOST: Kill
-Turn it off!

492
00:33:45,690 --> 00:33:47,526
-Kill. Kill
-FOON: Doctor!

493
00:33:47,609 --> 00:33:50,028
Kill. Kill. Kill

494
00:33:50,111 --> 00:33:51,947
-Go!
-Kill. Kill. Kill

495
00:33:52,030 --> 00:33:54,241
Hands frozen. Can't stop it.

496
00:33:54,324 --> 00:33:56,201
Come on! Double deadlock.

497
00:33:56,284 --> 00:33:57,619
Kill..

498
00:33:57,702 --> 00:34:00,205
-Go upstairs!
-Run, darling, run!

499
00:34:00,288 --> 00:34:06,002
Information.
Kill. Kill. Kill. Kill

500
00:34:06,086 --> 00:34:08,838
-Rickston, get them through.
-No chance.

501
00:34:10,090 --> 00:34:11,633
COPPER: Rickston!

502
00:34:11,716 --> 00:34:14,594
-I'll never get through there.
-Yes, you can. Let me clear...

503
00:34:14,678 --> 00:34:17,138
Kill. Kill. Kill

504
00:34:18,932 --> 00:34:22,060
It's the Host. They've gone berserk.
Can you cope up there?

505
00:34:24,145 --> 00:34:26,356
(GROANING)

506
00:34:28,233 --> 00:34:31,528
Kill. Kill. Kill. Kill...

507
00:34:33,113 --> 00:34:34,823
No, I'm stuck!

508
00:34:34,948 --> 00:34:36,741
ASTRID: Come on, you can do it.

509
00:34:36,825 --> 00:34:38,410
I can't!

510
00:34:39,286 --> 00:34:41,079
It's going to collapse.

511
00:34:42,831 --> 00:34:46,543
-Rickston, damn it, help me!
-No way.

512
00:34:46,668 --> 00:34:48,253
Morvin, get through!

513
00:34:48,336 --> 00:34:49,754
Ow!

514
00:34:51,965 --> 00:34:53,883
Kill. Kill

515
00:34:55,969 --> 00:34:57,596
ASTRID: Doctor, he's stuck.

516
00:34:57,679 --> 00:35:01,308
Mr Van Hoff, I know we've only just met,
but you'll have to excuse me.

517
00:35:02,100 --> 00:35:04,019
ASTRID: That's it. We've got you.

518
00:35:04,102 --> 00:35:05,937
-Kill. Kill...
-Doctor, come on, get through.

519
00:35:06,021 --> 00:35:07,105
Information override.

520
00:35:07,188 --> 00:35:09,316
You will tell me the point of origin
of your command structure.

521
00:35:09,399 --> 00:35:12,986
-I can't hold it.
-Information. Deck 31.

522
00:35:13,069 --> 00:35:17,282
-Thank you.
-Kill. Kill. Kill...

523
00:35:17,365 --> 00:35:18,867
Copper!

524
00:35:25,206 --> 00:35:27,125
(SCREAMING)

525
00:35:35,800 --> 00:35:38,553
Morvin, look, food.

526
00:35:38,637 --> 00:35:40,722
Oh, great! Someone's happy.

527
00:35:40,805 --> 00:35:42,849
Don't have any, then.

528
00:35:42,932 --> 00:35:44,351
(INTERCOM WHISTLING)

529
00:35:44,434 --> 00:35:46,561
-Mr Frame, you still there?
-Yes, sir.

530
00:35:46,686 --> 00:35:48,688
But I've got Host outside.

531
00:35:48,813 --> 00:35:50,190
I've sealed the door.

532
00:35:50,273 --> 00:35:52,525
They've been programmed to kill.
Why would anyone do that?

533
00:35:52,609 --> 00:35:55,612
That's not the only problem, Doctor.

534
00:35:55,737 --> 00:35:58,323
I had to use the maximum deadlock
on the door,

535
00:35:58,406 --> 00:36:02,410
which means no one can get in.

536
00:36:03,536 --> 00:36:05,163
I'm sealed off.

537
00:36:05,997 --> 00:36:08,917
Even if you can fix the Titanic,
you can't get to the bridge.

538
00:36:09,000 --> 00:36:13,254
Yeah, right, fine. One problem
at a time. What is on Deck 31?

539
00:36:13,338 --> 00:36:16,883
Er, that's down below. There's nothing.

540
00:36:17,676 --> 00:36:21,137
It's just the Host storage deck.
That's where we keep the robots.

541
00:36:22,389 --> 00:36:26,685
What's that? You see that panel? Black.

542
00:36:26,768 --> 00:36:30,271
It's registering nothing,
no power, no heat, no light.

543
00:36:30,397 --> 00:36:34,651
-Never seen it before.
-100% shielded. What's down there?

544
00:36:34,776 --> 00:36:37,153
I'll try intensifying the scanner.

545
00:36:37,278 --> 00:36:40,198
Let me know if you find anything,
and keep those engines going.

546
00:36:40,281 --> 00:36:41,950
Saved you some.

547
00:36:42,075 --> 00:36:45,120
You might be a Time King from Gannaby,
but you still need to eat.

548
00:36:45,245 --> 00:36:46,955
Yeah, thanks.

549
00:36:47,789 --> 00:36:49,749
But you look good for 903.

550
00:36:49,833 --> 00:36:52,627
-You should see me in the mornings.
-Okay.

551
00:36:56,423 --> 00:37:01,261
Doctor, it must be well past midnight,
Earth time.

552
00:37:01,386 --> 00:37:02,971
Christmas Day.

553
00:37:03,054 --> 00:37:05,014
So it is. Merry Christmas.

554
00:37:05,765 --> 00:37:08,560
This Christmas thing,
what's it all about?

555
00:37:09,144 --> 00:37:11,646
Long story. I should know, I was there.

556
00:37:12,313 --> 00:37:13,732
I got the last room.

557
00:37:13,815 --> 00:37:17,277
But if the planet's waking up,
can't we signal them?

558
00:37:17,360 --> 00:37:20,029
They could send up a rocket
or something.

559
00:37:20,113 --> 00:37:21,740
They don't have spaceships.

560
00:37:21,823 --> 00:37:24,367
No, I've read about it.
They have shuffles.

561
00:37:24,492 --> 00:37:26,578
Space shuffles.

562
00:37:26,661 --> 00:37:30,665
Mr Copper, this degree in Earthonomics,
where is it from?

563
00:37:34,377 --> 00:37:36,212
Honestly?

564
00:37:36,296 --> 00:37:38,298
Just between us.

565
00:37:39,382 --> 00:37:45,346
Mrs Golightly's Happy Travelling
University and Dry Cleaners.

566
00:37:47,182 --> 00:37:50,018
You lied to the company?

567
00:37:50,518 --> 00:37:51,936
To get the job?

568
00:37:52,020 --> 00:37:55,356
I wasted my life on Sto.

569
00:37:57,192 --> 00:38:00,528
I was a travelling salesman,
always on the road.

570
00:38:01,780 --> 00:38:06,201
And I reached retirement
with nothing to show for it.

571
00:38:06,284 --> 00:38:07,911
Not even a home.

572
00:38:09,788 --> 00:38:12,874
And Earth sounded so exotic.

573
00:38:12,999 --> 00:38:14,209
Mmm.

574
00:38:14,292 --> 00:38:17,545
-I suppose it is, yeah.
-How come you know it so well?

575
00:38:18,880 --> 00:38:20,590
I was sort of...

576
00:38:21,382 --> 00:38:23,802
A few years ago, I was sort of made...

577
00:38:23,885 --> 00:38:26,346
Well, sort of homeless and...

578
00:38:27,680 --> 00:38:30,099
There was the Earth.

579
00:38:30,183 --> 00:38:32,685
The thing is, if we survive this,
there'll be police

580
00:38:32,769 --> 00:38:35,146
and all sorts of investigations.

581
00:38:35,230 --> 00:38:38,107
Now, the minimum penalty
for space-lane fraud

582
00:38:38,191 --> 00:38:40,485
is 10 years in jail.

583
00:38:43,863 --> 00:38:45,907
I'm an old man.

584
00:38:46,407 --> 00:38:48,701
Well, I won't survive 10 years.

585
00:38:49,202 --> 00:38:50,245
(BANGING)

586
00:38:50,328 --> 00:38:52,664
The Host! Move, come on.

587
00:39:16,312 --> 00:39:19,357
-Is that the only way across?
-On the other hand, it is a way across.

588
00:39:19,440 --> 00:39:21,067
The engines are open.

589
00:39:21,150 --> 00:39:25,029
DOCTOR: Nuclear storm drive.
As soon as it stops, the 7itanicfalls.

590
00:39:25,113 --> 00:39:27,949
But that thing,
it'll never take our weight.

591
00:39:28,032 --> 00:39:29,242
You're going last, mate.

592
00:39:29,325 --> 00:39:31,202
It's nitrophine metal,
it's stronger than it looks.

593
00:39:31,286 --> 00:39:33,955
All the same, Rickston is right.
Me and Foon should...

594
00:39:34,080 --> 00:39:35,915
(SCREAMING)

595
00:39:35,999 --> 00:39:38,126
Morvin!

596
00:39:42,171 --> 00:39:44,549
I told you. I told you!

597
00:39:44,632 --> 00:39:46,467
Just shut up! Shut up!

598
00:39:46,551 --> 00:39:48,845
Bring him back.
Can't you bring him back?

599
00:39:48,970 --> 00:39:50,346
Bring him back, Doctor.

600
00:39:50,471 --> 00:39:52,640
-I can't, I'm sorry. I can't.
-You promised me.

601
00:39:52,765 --> 00:39:55,143
I know. I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

602
00:39:56,519 --> 00:40:00,732
Look, I rather think that
those things have got our scent.

603
00:40:00,815 --> 00:40:03,860
-I'm not waiting.
-DOCTOR: Careful! Take it slowly!

604
00:40:08,573 --> 00:40:10,408
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

605
00:40:11,701 --> 00:40:14,078
-Help me!
-You're okay.

606
00:40:14,162 --> 00:40:17,874
A step at a time.
Come on, you can do it.

607
00:40:17,999 --> 00:40:20,293
Kill. Kill..

608
00:40:20,376 --> 00:40:22,337
They're getting nearer.

609
00:40:22,420 --> 00:40:24,213
I'll seal us in.

610
00:40:24,297 --> 00:40:27,216
Leaving us trapped, wouldn't you say?

611
00:40:27,342 --> 00:40:30,261
Never say "trapped"”,
just inconveniently circumstanced.

612
00:40:30,345 --> 00:40:31,721
Oh!

613
00:40:35,475 --> 00:40:37,810
-I'm okay.
-Maybe he's all right.

614
00:40:37,894 --> 00:40:41,814
Maybe there's a gravity curve down there
or something, I don't know.

615
00:40:41,898 --> 00:40:43,691
Maybe he's just unconscious.

616
00:40:43,775 --> 00:40:47,153
I'm sorry, Foon, he's gone.

617
00:40:49,697 --> 00:40:52,992
I can't live without him...

618
00:40:54,035 --> 00:40:55,870
(CREAKING)

619
00:40:57,789 --> 00:41:01,542
Yes! Oh, yes! Who's good!

620
00:41:01,709 --> 00:41:04,504
-Bannakaffalatta, you go next.
-Bannakaffalatta is small.

621
00:41:04,587 --> 00:41:05,838
Slowly!

622
00:41:07,090 --> 00:41:08,424
(THUDDING)

623
00:41:08,508 --> 00:41:10,426
They've found us.

624
00:41:10,551 --> 00:41:12,637
Astrid, get across right now.

625
00:41:12,720 --> 00:41:14,847
-What about you?
-Just do it, go on.

626
00:41:14,931 --> 00:41:17,517
Mr Copper, we can't wait. Don't argue.

627
00:41:17,600 --> 00:41:18,726
(THUDDING)

628
00:41:18,810 --> 00:41:21,104
Foon, you've got to get across
right now.

629
00:41:21,229 --> 00:41:25,316
What for?
What am I going to do without him?

630
00:41:25,400 --> 00:41:27,777
Doctor! The door is locked.

631
00:41:27,860 --> 00:41:30,071
Just think, what would he want, eh?

632
00:41:30,154 --> 00:41:33,032
He don't want nothing. He's dead.

633
00:41:34,283 --> 00:41:36,577
Doctor, I can't open the door!

634
00:41:36,661 --> 00:41:38,746
We need the whirring key thing of yours.

635
00:41:38,871 --> 00:41:39,956
I can't leave her!

636
00:41:40,039 --> 00:41:42,625
She'll get us all killed
if we can't get out.

637
00:41:48,256 --> 00:41:51,592
Mrs Van Hoff, I'm coming back for you.
All right?

638
00:41:57,640 --> 00:41:59,225
(CREAKING)

639
00:41:59,308 --> 00:42:00,601
Too many people.

640
00:42:00,727 --> 00:42:03,563
Oi, don't get spiky with me, keep going.

641
00:42:03,646 --> 00:42:05,648
(THUDDING CONTINUES)

642
00:42:17,785 --> 00:42:19,078
Careful!

643
00:42:19,162 --> 00:42:21,789
It's just settling, keep going.

644
00:42:21,914 --> 00:42:23,541
(THUDDING STOPS)

645
00:42:27,670 --> 00:42:29,464
They've stopped.

646
00:42:29,547 --> 00:42:30,923
Gone away?

647
00:42:31,007 --> 00:42:32,842
But why would they give up?

648
00:42:33,509 --> 00:42:35,803
Never mind that, keep coming.

649
00:42:36,637 --> 00:42:38,306
Where have they gone?

650
00:42:39,015 --> 00:42:41,309
Where are the Host?

651
00:42:44,187 --> 00:42:48,191
Well, I'm afraid,
we forgot the traditions of Christmas.

652
00:42:48,316 --> 00:42:51,694
That angels have wings.

653
00:43:03,539 --> 00:43:04,832
Information.

654
00:43:04,916 --> 00:43:06,334
Kill.

655
00:43:06,417 --> 00:43:08,920
Arm yourself, all of you!

656
00:43:11,297 --> 00:43:12,965
(GRUNTING)

657
00:43:26,187 --> 00:43:27,480
No!

658
00:43:31,067 --> 00:43:32,652
(SCREAMS)

659
00:43:35,947 --> 00:43:39,033
-I can't.
-Bannakaffalatta stop.

660
00:43:40,368 --> 00:43:42,370
Bannakaffalatta proud.

661
00:43:43,621 --> 00:43:46,207
Bannakaffalatta cyborg!

662
00:44:07,103 --> 00:44:09,981
Electromagnetic pulse
took out the robotics.

663
00:44:10,064 --> 00:44:12,400
Oh, Bannakaffalatta, that was brilliant.

664
00:44:20,700 --> 00:44:22,910
He's used all his power.

665
00:44:22,994 --> 00:44:24,370
Did good?

666
00:44:25,163 --> 00:44:27,081
You saved our lives.

667
00:44:27,748 --> 00:44:29,959
Bannakaffalatta happy.

668
00:44:30,585 --> 00:44:31,794
We can recharge you,

669
00:44:31,878 --> 00:44:34,255
get you to a power point,
just plug you in.

670
00:44:35,256 --> 00:44:37,049
Too late.

671
00:44:37,758 --> 00:44:41,846
No, but... You've got to
get me that drink, remember?

672
00:44:43,723 --> 00:44:45,516
Pretty girl.

673
00:44:59,280 --> 00:45:01,866
-I'm sorry, forgive me.
-Leave him alone.

674
00:45:01,991 --> 00:45:04,952
It's the EMP transmitter.

675
00:45:06,078 --> 00:45:10,541
He'd want us to use it.
I used to sell these things.

676
00:45:10,625 --> 00:45:13,753
They'd always give me a bed
for the night in the cyborg caravans.

677
00:45:13,836 --> 00:45:15,963
They're good people.

678
00:45:16,756 --> 00:45:19,050
But if we can recharge it,

679
00:45:19,133 --> 00:45:22,386
we can use it as a weapon
against the rest of the Host.

680
00:45:22,470 --> 00:45:24,722
Bannakaffalatta might have saved us all.

681
00:45:24,805 --> 00:45:27,475
Do you think? Try telling him that.

682
00:45:30,144 --> 00:45:32,271
-Information. Reboot.
-Use the EMP!

683
00:45:32,355 --> 00:45:34,273
-It's dead.
-It's got to have emergency...

684
00:45:34,357 --> 00:45:36,567
No, no. Hold on.
Hold the line. Loophole.

685
00:45:36,651 --> 00:45:40,696
Security protocol 10...666...21.

686
00:45:40,821 --> 00:45:42,740
Four, five, six, seven, eight...

687
00:45:42,823 --> 00:45:46,619
I don't know, 427 One!

688
00:45:49,830 --> 00:45:52,333
Information. State request.

689
00:45:53,751 --> 00:45:55,920
Good. Right.

690
00:45:56,629 --> 00:45:58,714
You've been ordered
to kill the survivors, but why?

691
00:45:58,798 --> 00:46:01,259
Information. No witnesses.

692
00:46:01,384 --> 00:46:03,719
But this ship's going to fall
on the Earth and kill everyone.

693
00:46:03,844 --> 00:46:05,513
The human race has got
nothing to do with the Titanic

694
00:46:05,638 --> 00:46:07,265
so that contravenes your orders, yes?

695
00:46:07,348 --> 00:46:09,600
Information. Incorrect.

696
00:46:09,684 --> 00:46:11,686
But why do you want
to destroy the Earth?

697
00:46:11,769 --> 00:46:15,273
-Information. It is the plan.
-What plan?

698
00:46:15,356 --> 00:46:18,609
Information. The protocol
grants you only three questions.

699
00:46:18,693 --> 00:46:21,612
These three questions have been used.

700
00:46:21,696 --> 00:46:25,741
-Well, you could have warned me.
-Information. Now you will die.

701
00:46:32,581 --> 00:46:34,417
You're coming with me.

702
00:46:38,879 --> 00:46:40,256
No!

703
00:46:59,025 --> 00:47:00,901
No more.

704
00:47:04,613 --> 00:47:06,574
Right, get yourself
over to Reception One.

705
00:47:06,657 --> 00:47:09,118
Once you're there, Mr Copper,
you've got staff access to the computer.

706
00:47:09,243 --> 00:47:11,954
Try to find a way transmitting an SOS.
Astrid, you're in charge of this.

707
00:47:12,038 --> 00:47:14,206
Once it's powered up,
it'll take out Host within 50 yards,

708
00:47:14,290 --> 00:47:16,334
but then it needs 60 seconds
to recharge. Got it?

709
00:47:16,417 --> 00:47:18,044
Rickston, take this.

710
00:47:18,127 --> 00:47:20,504
I've preset it, just hold down
that button, it'll open the doors.

711
00:47:20,588 --> 00:47:22,256
Do not lose it!

712
00:47:22,340 --> 00:47:25,176
You got that?
Now, go open the next door.

713
00:47:25,384 --> 00:47:27,011
-Go on! Go!
-All right.

714
00:47:27,094 --> 00:47:29,096
Mr Copper, I need you fighting fit.

715
00:47:29,180 --> 00:47:32,058
-Astrid, where's the power points?
-Under the comms.

716
00:47:33,559 --> 00:47:37,063
It'll beep when it's ready.
That blue light comes on there.

717
00:47:37,146 --> 00:47:39,273
You're talking as if
you're not coming with us.

718
00:47:39,398 --> 00:47:41,817
There's something down on Deck 31.
I'm going to find out what it is.

719
00:47:41,942 --> 00:47:45,738
-What if you meet a Host?
-Well, then I'll just have some fun.

720
00:47:46,530 --> 00:47:48,491
Sounds like you do this kind of thing
all the time.

721
00:47:48,616 --> 00:47:50,534
Not by choice.

722
00:47:50,618 --> 00:47:53,662
All I do is travel.
That's what I am, just a traveller.

723
00:47:54,622 --> 00:47:57,958
Imagine it. No tax, no bills, no boss.

724
00:47:58,084 --> 00:47:59,794
Just the open sky.

725
00:48:02,088 --> 00:48:05,716
I'm sort of unemployed now.

726
00:48:06,884 --> 00:48:10,304
I was thinking
that blue box is kind of small,

727
00:48:10,388 --> 00:48:13,641
but I could squeeze in like a stowaway.

728
00:48:14,725 --> 00:48:15,893
It's not always safe.

729
00:48:15,976 --> 00:48:17,436
So you need someone to take care of you.

730
00:48:17,520 --> 00:48:21,148
I've got no one back on Sto, no family.
Just me.

731
00:48:25,528 --> 00:48:27,488
So what do you think?

732
00:48:28,155 --> 00:48:30,282
Can I come with you?

733
00:48:33,619 --> 00:48:35,454
Yeah, I'd like that. Yeah.

734
00:48:40,334 --> 00:48:43,796
-Mr Frame, you still with us?
-It's the engines, sir. Final phase.

735
00:48:43,879 --> 00:48:47,258
There's nothing more I can do.
We've only got eight minutes left.

736
00:48:47,341 --> 00:48:50,386
-Don't worry, I'll get there.
-But the bridge is sealed off.

737
00:48:50,469 --> 00:48:52,930
Yeah, yeah, working on it.
I'll get there, Mr Frame, somehow.

738
00:48:57,977 --> 00:48:59,645
DOCTOR: You charged up?

739
00:48:59,728 --> 00:49:02,982
Mr Copper, look after her.
Astrid, look after him.

740
00:49:03,065 --> 00:49:06,777
Rickston, look after yourself.
And I'll see you again.

741
00:49:07,445 --> 00:49:09,280
-I promise.
-Hold on.

742
00:49:09,363 --> 00:49:10,698
There's an old tradition on planet Sto.

743
00:49:10,781 --> 00:49:13,742
-Yeah, I have really got to go.
-Just wait a minute.

744
00:49:22,501 --> 00:49:26,255
Yeah, that's a...
Very old tradition, yeah.

745
00:49:29,133 --> 00:49:31,427
-See you later.
-Oh, yes.

746
00:49:46,984 --> 00:49:48,903
Do it!

747
00:50:09,590 --> 00:50:11,550
Wait, wait, wait, wait!
Security protocol one.

748
00:50:11,634 --> 00:50:13,719
Do you hear me? One! One!

749
00:50:14,762 --> 00:50:18,599
Okay. That gives me three questions.

750
00:50:18,724 --> 00:50:20,809
Three questions to
save my life, am I right?

751
00:50:20,893 --> 00:50:23,521
Information. Correct.

752
00:50:23,604 --> 00:50:25,856
No, that wasn't one of them.
I didn't mean it. That's not fair!

753
00:50:25,940 --> 00:50:28,651
-Can I start again?
-Information. No.

754
00:50:28,776 --> 00:50:32,112
No! No, no, no.
That wasn't a question either. Blimey!

755
00:50:33,656 --> 00:50:36,534
One question left. One question.

756
00:50:36,617 --> 00:50:39,203
So, you've been given orders to
kill the survivors,

757
00:50:39,286 --> 00:50:41,080
but survivors must therefore

758
00:50:41,163 --> 00:50:44,917
be passengers or staff, but not me,
I'm not a passenger, I'm not staff.

759
00:50:45,000 --> 00:50:46,627
Go on. Scan me.

760
00:50:46,710 --> 00:50:48,796
You must have bio records,
no such person on board.

761
00:50:48,963 --> 00:50:53,384
I don't exist,
therefore you can't kill me,

762
00:50:53,467 --> 00:50:55,636
therefore I'm a stowaway.

763
00:50:56,512 --> 00:50:58,264
And stowaways should be arrested

764
00:50:58,347 --> 00:51:01,225
and taken to the nearest figure
of authority.

765
00:51:01,308 --> 00:51:05,145
And I reckon,
the nearest figure of authority

766
00:51:05,312 --> 00:51:06,855
is on Deck 31.

767
00:51:07,731 --> 00:51:09,984
Final question, am I right?

768
00:51:10,067 --> 00:51:13,737
-Information. Correct.
-Brilliant.

769
00:51:14,655 --> 00:51:16,740
Take me to your leader.

770
00:51:17,658 --> 00:51:19,451
I've always wanted to say that.

771
00:51:35,426 --> 00:51:39,638
Rickston, seal the doors,
make the room secure.

772
00:51:39,722 --> 00:51:42,850
Mr Copper, keep an eye on the Host.
I need to check the computer.

773
00:51:42,933 --> 00:51:44,810
We need that SOS.

774
00:52:00,909 --> 00:52:04,330
Bridge, this is Reception One.

775
00:52:04,413 --> 00:52:08,334
-Who's that?
-Astrid Peth, I was with the Doctor.

776
00:52:08,417 --> 00:52:11,420
Tell me, can you divert power
to the teleport system?

777
00:52:11,503 --> 00:52:14,006
No way, I'm using everything I've got
to keep the engines going.

778
00:52:14,089 --> 00:52:17,551
It's just one trip.
I need to get to Deck 31.

779
00:52:17,676 --> 00:52:19,845
And I'm telling you, no!

780
00:52:21,972 --> 00:52:25,559
Mr Frame, this is for the Doctor.

781
00:52:27,311 --> 00:52:31,231
He's gone down there on his own and I...

782
00:52:31,940 --> 00:52:36,195
I can't just leave him.
He's done everything he can to save us.

783
00:52:38,280 --> 00:52:41,158
It's time we did something to help him.

784
00:52:43,577 --> 00:52:45,329
Giving you power.

785
00:52:50,459 --> 00:52:53,462
Mr Copper, I'm going to find him.

786
00:52:54,254 --> 00:52:56,173
Good luck.

787
00:53:11,355 --> 00:53:13,023
DOCTOR: Wow.

788
00:53:13,899 --> 00:53:17,611
Now, that is what you call
a fixer-upper.

789
00:53:19,446 --> 00:53:20,572
Come on, then.

790
00:53:20,656 --> 00:53:24,618
Host with the most, this ultimate
authority of yours, who is it?

791
00:53:25,703 --> 00:53:27,913
Oh! That's clever!

792
00:53:29,289 --> 00:53:31,875
That's an Omnistate impact chamber.

793
00:53:32,292 --> 00:53:36,171
Indestructible. You could
survive anything in there.

794
00:53:36,255 --> 00:53:39,800
You could sit through a supernova.
Or a shipwreck.

795
00:53:40,843 --> 00:53:43,470
Only one person could have
the power and the money

796
00:53:43,554 --> 00:53:46,098
to hide themselves on board like this.

797
00:53:46,849 --> 00:53:48,851
And I should know 'cause...

798
00:53:48,976 --> 00:53:53,147
My name is Max.

799
00:53:53,647 --> 00:53:55,899
-It really does that?
-Who the hell is this?

800
00:53:55,983 --> 00:53:57,985
I'm the Doctor, hello!

801
00:53:58,068 --> 00:54:00,696
Information. Stowaway.

802
00:54:00,779 --> 00:54:01,905
-Well...
-Kill him!

803
00:54:01,989 --> 00:54:05,826
Oh, no, no, no, no, wait!
You can't, not now, come on, Max.

804
00:54:05,909 --> 00:54:10,873
You'll give me so much good material,
like how to get ahead in business.

805
00:54:11,498 --> 00:54:14,835
See, head. Head. Head in the... No?

806
00:54:14,960 --> 00:54:19,298
Oh! The office joker.
I like a funny man.

807
00:54:20,215 --> 00:54:23,552
No one's been funny with me for years.

808
00:54:23,635 --> 00:54:25,471
I can't think why.

809
00:54:25,554 --> 00:54:29,933
176 years of running the company
have taken their toll.

810
00:54:30,017 --> 00:54:35,647
-Yeah, but nice wheels.
-No! A life support system.

811
00:54:36,565 --> 00:54:41,445
In a society that despises cyborgs,
I've had to hide away for years.

812
00:54:41,528 --> 00:54:46,283
Running the company by hologram.
Host, situation report.

813
00:54:46,617 --> 00:54:48,577
Information.

814
00:54:48,660 --> 00:54:51,121
Titanic ls still in orbit.

815
00:54:52,998 --> 00:54:54,416
Let me see.

816
00:54:56,710 --> 00:55:00,297
Should have crashed by now.
What's gone wrong?

817
00:55:03,383 --> 00:55:07,429
The engines are still running!
They should have stopped.

818
00:55:07,513 --> 00:55:09,807
When they do, the Earth gets roasted.
I don't understand.

819
00:55:09,890 --> 00:55:11,725
What's the Earth got to do with it?

820
00:55:11,850 --> 00:55:15,145
This interview is terminated!

821
00:55:15,896 --> 00:55:20,400
No, no, no, no! Hold on! Hold on!
Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait!

822
00:55:20,484 --> 00:55:22,277
I can work it out.

823
00:55:22,402 --> 00:55:25,364
It's like a task.
I'm your apprentice, just watch me.

824
00:55:25,447 --> 00:55:29,117
So, the business is failing
and you wreck the ship,

825
00:55:29,243 --> 00:55:31,620
so that makes things even worse.
Oh, yes!

826
00:55:31,745 --> 00:55:34,915
No... Yes.

827
00:55:35,499 --> 00:55:39,586
The business isn't failing, it's failed.
Past tense.

828
00:55:40,629 --> 00:55:43,090
My own board voted me out.

829
00:55:43,173 --> 00:55:45,425
-Stabbed me in the back!
-If you had a back.

830
00:55:45,509 --> 00:55:48,887
So, you scupper the ship,
wipe out any survivors,

831
00:55:48,971 --> 00:55:50,597
just in case anyone's rumbled you,

832
00:55:50,681 --> 00:55:54,268
and the Board find
their shares halved in value.

833
00:55:54,393 --> 00:55:56,520
Oh, but that's not enough.

834
00:55:58,814 --> 00:55:59,940
No.

835
00:56:00,774 --> 00:56:05,362
Because if a Max Capricorn ship hits
the Earth, it destroys an entire planet.

836
00:56:05,445 --> 00:56:07,823
Outrage back home. Scandal!

837
00:56:08,574 --> 00:56:10,367
The business is wiped out.

838
00:56:10,450 --> 00:56:14,454
And the whole Board

839
00:56:14,580 --> 00:56:18,542
thrown in jail for mass murder.

840
00:56:18,625 --> 00:56:21,628
While you sit there
safe inside the impact chamber.

841
00:56:21,712 --> 00:56:25,966
I have men waiting to
retrieve me from the ruins,

842
00:56:26,049 --> 00:56:28,719
and enough off-world accounts
to retire me

843
00:56:28,802 --> 00:56:31,179
to the beaches of Penhaxico II.

844
00:56:31,263 --> 00:56:37,311
Where the ladies, so I'm told,
are very fond of metal.

845
00:56:38,145 --> 00:56:40,063
So that's the plan?

846
00:56:40,147 --> 00:56:43,650
A retirement plan.
2,000 people on this ship,

847
00:56:44,568 --> 00:56:48,655
six billion underneath us,
all of them slaughtered! And why?

848
00:56:48,780 --> 00:56:51,909
Because Max Capricorn is a loser!

849
00:56:52,659 --> 00:56:55,245
I never lose!

850
00:56:55,329 --> 00:56:59,958
-You can't even sink the Titanic!
-Oh, but I can, Doctor!

851
00:57:00,918 --> 00:57:04,338
I can cancel the engines from here!

852
00:57:06,006 --> 00:57:07,132
(ALARM BLARING)

853
00:57:07,215 --> 00:57:09,092
ELECTRONIC VOICE: Engines closing.

854
00:57:09,176 --> 00:57:12,054
-No, no, no, no, no!
-Engines closing.

855
00:57:12,137 --> 00:57:14,389
Engines closing.

856
00:57:16,016 --> 00:57:17,267
What's happening?

857
00:57:17,351 --> 00:57:20,103
-You can't do this!
-Host, hold him!

858
00:57:22,272 --> 00:57:24,691
Not so clever now, Doctor.

859
00:57:25,317 --> 00:57:28,779
It's a shame we couldn't work together.
You're rather good.

860
00:57:28,862 --> 00:57:32,324
All that banter, yet not a word wasted.

861
00:57:32,407 --> 00:57:34,868
Time for me to retire.

862
00:57:35,577 --> 00:57:40,540
The Titanicis falling,
the sky will burn!

863
00:57:41,500 --> 00:57:45,420
Let the Christmas inferno commence!

864
00:57:46,463 --> 00:57:48,215
Oh! Host!

865
00:57:49,883 --> 00:57:51,843
Kill him!

866
00:57:53,387 --> 00:57:55,263
Mr Capricorn!

867
00:57:59,393 --> 00:58:00,936
I resign.

868
00:58:05,399 --> 00:58:07,109
Astrid, don't!

869
00:58:28,463 --> 00:58:30,674
DOCTOR: He's cut the brake line!

870
00:58:37,014 --> 00:58:39,349
(SILENT) No.

871
00:59:01,371 --> 00:59:03,540
Astrid!

872
00:59:27,564 --> 00:59:29,983
ELECTRONIC VOICE: Titanic falling.

873
00:59:30,776 --> 00:59:32,652
Voyage terminated.

874
00:59:34,404 --> 00:59:36,948
Voyage terminated.

875
01:01:00,907 --> 01:01:02,993
ELECTRONIC VOICE: Deadlock broken.

876
01:01:03,076 --> 01:01:05,328
Midshipman Frame, at last!

877
01:01:06,538 --> 01:01:07,664
But the Host?

878
01:01:07,747 --> 01:01:10,417
Controller dead, they divert
to the next highest authority.

879
01:01:10,500 --> 01:01:12,586
-And that's me.
-There's nothing we can do.

880
01:01:12,669 --> 01:01:14,880
There's no power. The ships gonna fall.

881
01:01:15,714 --> 01:01:18,091
ELECTRONIC VOICE: Titanic falling.

882
01:01:18,800 --> 01:01:21,052
-What's your first name?
-Alonzo.

883
01:01:21,136 --> 01:01:23,013
Titanic falling.

884
01:01:23,096 --> 01:01:25,557
-You're kidding me.
-What?

885
01:01:25,682 --> 01:01:28,101
That's something else
I've always wanted to say.

886
01:01:28,185 --> 01:01:30,395
Allons-y, Alonzo!

887
01:01:41,573 --> 01:01:45,035
(ALARM BLARING)

888
01:02:21,071 --> 01:02:23,698
(BEEPING)

889
01:02:33,333 --> 01:02:36,836
Hello, yes, could you
get me Buckingham Palace?

890
01:02:36,920 --> 01:02:40,674
And as dawn rises over Great Britain,
it seems that this year

891
01:02:40,799 --> 01:02:44,135
the city of London
has escaped alien intervention.

892
01:02:44,886 --> 01:02:50,016
The Queen has remained in residence
in defiance of extraterrestrial attack.

893
01:02:50,100 --> 01:02:53,436
Listen to me, security code 771.
Now get out of there!

894
01:02:53,895 --> 01:02:55,188
MAN: Open the door!

895
01:02:55,313 --> 01:02:56,606
(DOG WHIMPERING)

896
01:03:00,360 --> 01:03:05,448
Don't you dare! You aliens!
Don't you dare!

897
01:03:11,871 --> 01:03:15,625
ELECTRONIC VOICE: Engine active.
Engine active.

898
01:03:42,944 --> 01:03:47,699
QUEEN: Thank you, Doctor. Thank you.
Happy Christmas!

899
01:03:47,782 --> 01:03:49,409
(DOGS BARKING)

900
01:03:58,835 --> 01:04:01,254
(LAUGHING)

901
01:04:01,588 --> 01:04:03,923
Yes! Oh, yes!

902
01:04:08,928 --> 01:04:10,680
(BELL CLANGING)

903
01:04:14,267 --> 01:04:16,478
Whoo!

904
01:04:31,451 --> 01:04:35,413
Use the heat of re-entry
to fire up a secondary storm drive.

905
01:04:36,373 --> 01:04:38,375
Unsinkable, that's me.

906
01:04:40,126 --> 01:04:41,586
We made it.

907
01:04:42,337 --> 01:04:44,297
Not all of us.

908
01:04:47,634 --> 01:04:49,094
Teleport!

909
01:04:50,261 --> 01:04:52,430
She was wearing a teleport bracelet.

910
01:04:53,973 --> 01:04:55,683
Rickston! Sonic!

911
01:04:56,518 --> 01:04:59,062
Mr Copper, the teleports,
have they got emergency settings?

912
01:04:59,145 --> 01:05:02,524
-I don't know, they should have.
-She fell. Mr Copper, she fell.

913
01:05:02,649 --> 01:05:04,442
-What's the emergency code?
-Let me see.

914
01:05:04,526 --> 01:05:07,320
-What the hell are you doing?
-We can bring her back.

915
01:05:08,780 --> 01:05:10,698
If a passenger has an accident
on shore leave

916
01:05:10,824 --> 01:05:12,617
and they're still
wearing their teleport,

917
01:05:12,700 --> 01:05:15,870
the molecules are automatically
suspended and held in stasis.

918
01:05:15,954 --> 01:05:19,582
-So if we can just trigger the ship's...
-There!

919
01:05:19,666 --> 01:05:23,128
-ASTRID: I'm falling.
-Only halfway there. Come on!

920
01:05:23,211 --> 01:05:24,337
Keep falling.

921
01:05:24,462 --> 01:05:26,714
Feedback the molecule grid.
Boost it with the restoration matrix...

922
01:05:26,798 --> 01:05:28,341
No, no, no, no, no!

923
01:05:28,425 --> 01:05:29,884
-Need more phase containment.
-Doctor...

924
01:05:29,968 --> 01:05:32,053
No! If I can just link up
the surface suspension.

925
01:05:32,137 --> 01:05:35,098
-Doctor, she's gone.
-I just need to override the safety...

926
01:05:35,181 --> 01:05:37,350
I can do this! I can do it!

927
01:05:37,475 --> 01:05:39,769
Doctor, let her go.

928
01:05:44,899 --> 01:05:46,818
I can do anything!

929
01:05:47,193 --> 01:05:48,903
Stop me falling.

930
01:05:56,202 --> 01:06:00,206
There's not enough left.
The system is too badly damaged.

931
01:06:02,375 --> 01:06:04,836
She's just atoms, Doctor.

932
01:06:06,671 --> 01:06:10,216
An echo with the ghost of consciousness.

933
01:06:12,760 --> 01:06:14,387
She's stardust.

934
01:06:19,684 --> 01:06:23,062
Astrid Peth, citizen of Sto,

935
01:06:26,774 --> 01:06:30,737
the woman who looked at the stars
and dreamt of travelling.

936
01:06:38,077 --> 01:06:39,954
There's an old tradition.

937
01:06:54,135 --> 01:06:55,929
Now you can travel forever.

938
01:07:09,609 --> 01:07:11,861
You're not falling, Astrid,

939
01:07:13,154 --> 01:07:15,073
you're flying.

940
01:07:42,767 --> 01:07:45,979
The engines have stabilised.
We're holding steady till we get help,

941
01:07:46,104 --> 01:07:48,231
and I've sent the SOS.

942
01:07:49,148 --> 01:07:51,734
The rescue ship should
be here in 20 minutes.

943
01:07:51,818 --> 01:07:54,320
And they're digging out
the records on Max Capricorn.

944
01:07:54,445 --> 01:07:56,614
It should be quite a story.

945
01:07:57,198 --> 01:08:00,159
They'll want to talk
to all of us, I suppose.

946
01:08:00,285 --> 01:08:02,412
I'd have thought so, yeah.

947
01:08:03,246 --> 01:08:07,500
I think one or two inconvenient truths
might come to light.

948
01:08:08,585 --> 01:08:10,837
It's my own fault.

949
01:08:10,920 --> 01:08:14,007
And 10 years in jail
is better than dying.

950
01:08:17,093 --> 01:08:19,012
(SOBBING) Doctor,

951
01:08:19,679 --> 01:08:21,180
I never said...

952
01:08:22,181 --> 01:08:23,891
Thank you.

953
01:08:31,649 --> 01:08:33,484
The funny thing is,

954
01:08:34,736 --> 01:08:37,572
I said Max Capricorn was falling apart.

955
01:08:38,197 --> 01:08:41,451
Just before the crash,
I sold all my shares.

956
01:08:42,493 --> 01:08:44,912
Transferred them to his rivals.

957
01:08:45,997 --> 01:08:47,749
It's made me rich.

958
01:08:48,708 --> 01:08:50,877
What do you think of that?

959
01:08:51,002 --> 01:08:53,212
(RINGING)

960
01:08:56,799 --> 01:09:01,721
Those shares, I want them
triple bonded and locked.

961
01:09:01,804 --> 01:09:07,894
Of all the people to survive, he's not
the one you would have chosen, is he?

962
01:09:10,438 --> 01:09:13,149
But if you could choose, Doctor,
if you could decide

963
01:09:13,232 --> 01:09:15,401
who lives and who dies,

964
01:09:17,111 --> 01:09:19,572
that would make you a monster.

965
01:09:24,911 --> 01:09:26,371
Mr Copper,

966
01:09:27,830 --> 01:09:31,292
I think you deserve one of these.

967
01:09:58,277 --> 01:10:02,407
COPPER: So, Great Britain
is part of Europy,

968
01:10:02,490 --> 01:10:04,367
and just across the British Channel

969
01:10:04,450 --> 01:10:06,786
you've got Great France
and Great Germany.

970
01:10:06,869 --> 01:10:10,957
No, no, it's just France and Germany.
Only Britain's "Great".

971
01:10:11,040 --> 01:10:15,044
And they're all at war
with the continent of Hamerica.

972
01:10:15,128 --> 01:10:17,338
No. Well, not yet.

973
01:10:18,923 --> 01:10:22,677
We can argue that one.
There she is. Survive anything.

974
01:10:24,804 --> 01:10:29,517
You know, between you and me,
I don't even think this snow is real.

975
01:10:29,600 --> 01:10:35,982
I think it's the ballast from the
Titanic salvage entering the atmosphere.

976
01:10:38,651 --> 01:10:42,155
Yeah. One of these days
it might snow for real.

977
01:10:44,198 --> 01:10:47,452
So, I suppose you'll be off.

978
01:10:47,535 --> 01:10:49,245
The open sky.

979
01:10:49,912 --> 01:10:51,789
And what about me?

980
01:10:53,958 --> 01:10:55,585
I travel alone.

981
01:10:56,252 --> 01:10:58,129
It's best that way.

982
01:10:59,672 --> 01:11:02,216
What am I supposed to do?

983
01:11:02,800 --> 01:11:04,969
Give me that credit card.

984
01:11:06,929 --> 01:11:09,974
Well, it's just petty cash,
spending money.

985
01:11:10,516 --> 01:11:13,561
It's all done by computer.
I didn't really know the currency,

986
01:11:13,644 --> 01:11:16,355
so I thought a million might cover it.

987
01:11:16,939 --> 01:11:19,025
A million? Pounds?

988
01:11:19,108 --> 01:11:21,360
Is that enough for trinkets?

989
01:11:21,986 --> 01:11:25,865
Mr Copper, a million pounds
is worth 50 million credits.

990
01:11:28,534 --> 01:11:32,497
-How much?
-50 million and 56.

991
01:11:37,126 --> 01:11:38,711
I've got money.

992
01:11:39,962 --> 01:11:41,464
Yes, you have.

993
01:11:42,799 --> 01:11:44,884
Oh, my word.

994
01:11:45,885 --> 01:11:50,681
Oh, my word! Oh, my goodness me!

995
01:11:52,058 --> 01:11:53,810
Yes!

996
01:11:53,893 --> 01:11:58,439
It's all yours, planet Earth.
Now that's a retirement plan.

997
01:11:58,523 --> 01:12:00,566
But just you be careful, though.

998
01:12:00,650 --> 01:12:02,485
I will. I will, oh, I will!

999
01:12:02,568 --> 01:12:06,113
No interfering.
I don't want any trouble, just...

1000
01:12:06,239 --> 01:12:07,907
Just have a nice life.

1001
01:12:07,990 --> 01:12:14,622
But I can have a house,
a proper house with a garden and a door!

1002
01:12:15,289 --> 01:12:18,751
Oh, Doctor, I will make you proud.

1003
01:12:21,420 --> 01:12:27,635
And I can have a kitchen
with chairs and windows and plates!

1004
01:12:32,390 --> 01:12:34,433
Where are you going?

1005
01:12:34,517 --> 01:12:36,102
I've no idea!

1006
01:12:36,936 --> 01:12:38,062
No.

1007
01:12:39,230 --> 01:12:40,648
Me neither.

1008
01:12:41,148 --> 01:12:42,942
But, Doctor!

1009
01:12:43,901 --> 01:12:45,736
I won't forget her.

1010
01:12:59,000 --> 01:13:01,252
Merry Christmas, Mr Copper.

1011
01:13:26,235 --> 01:13:27,403
Come with me.

1012
01:13:29,447 --> 01:13:32,825
The thrill is in the chase,
never in the capture.

1013
01:13:37,079 --> 01:13:39,040
There's nowhere to run.

1014
01:13:41,000 --> 01:13:42,585
Show yourself.

1015
01:13:43,336 --> 01:13:44,629
Doctor!

1016
01:13:45,588 --> 01:13:48,424
This is the spark of life.

1017
01:13:49,300 --> 01:13:53,095
-I just want a mate.
-You're not mating with me, sunshine.

1018
01:13:54,513 --> 01:13:57,433
Being with you, I can't tell what's
right and what's wrong any more.

1019
01:14:00,561 --> 01:14:02,104
It's better that way.

1020
01:14:02,188 --> 01:14:05,608
-I do not understand, Miss...
-Why'd you say "Miss". Do I look single?

1021
01:14:05,691 --> 01:14:06,734
Oh, yes!

1022
01:14:06,859 --> 01:14:08,986
I demand you tell me who you are!

1023
01:14:09,070 --> 01:14:12,156
(SHOUTING)

1024
01:14:22,041 --> 01:14:24,126
This has certainly been
a most entertaining evening.

